    <h1>My account</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">The new <strong>Ceres</strong> online store</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>As of now, online store projects are based on the new online store plugin  <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-ceres">Ceres</a>. The <strong>Ceres</strong> store uses the latest and future-proof <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/plugins">plugin technology</a>. Ceres can be customised easily and extended by additional plugins from the <a href="https://marketplace.plentymarkets.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plentyMarketplace</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Online stores that have been created on the basis of the old CMS will be maintained during the transition period. However, no new features will be developed for the old CMS. We recommend to use the new <strong>Ceres</strong> online store for all future online store projects.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_general_information_about_the_basic_settings">1. General information about the basic settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This menu contains basic settings for the individual customer area of your online store. Here you can select whether specific features should be activated or deactivated and which information should be displayed in the <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/cms#web-design-editing-the-web-design-my-account">My Account</a> area, for example weights and options for displaying the prices.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_configuration">2. Configuration</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The settings of this menu will be explained below in <a href="#table-my-account-settings">Table 1</a>. There you will also find references and links to further pages of the manual that provide detailed information about those settings and functions.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/assets/EN-Client-My-Account-Basic-Settings-01.png" alt="EN Client My Account Basic Settings 01">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 1. options in the <strong>Settings</strong> menu</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Configuring basic settings for the My Account area:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » My Account » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in the following table and carry out the settings as desired.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-my-account-settings" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
<caption class="title">Table 1. options in the <strong>Settings</strong> menu</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 25%;">
<col style="width: 75%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Customer login</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select which data your customers should use to log into the online store. The <strong>email address and password</strong> or the <strong>customer ID and password</strong>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Validity of checkout URL</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select how long a checkout URL should be valid after it was generated. You can select different options between <strong>7</strong> and <strong>360 days</strong> or you can select <strong>Never</strong>. If you select the option <strong>Never</strong>, then customers will have to log into the My Account area in order to access order information with the checkout URL.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Watchlist</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the watchlist in the online store.<br>
<em>*Info*</em>: The submenu under <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/cms#web-design-editing-the-web-design-my-account">CMS » Web design » My account</a> becomes visible once this function has been activated.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Wish list</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the <strong>wish list</strong>.<br>
<em>*Info*</em>: The submenu under <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/cms#web-design-editing-the-web-design-my-account">CMS » Web design » My account</a> becomes visible once this function has been activated.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Documents</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for downloading documents in the online store.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Data export</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for downloading data formats in the online store.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>My coupons</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for displaying the customer’s coupons.[#10]</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Return</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Specifies whether customers should be allowed to create returns within their own accounts.<br>
<strong>Activated</strong> = Customers can create returns. However, labels will not be provided. You will need to decide how you want to proceed when customers return items. For example, you can send customers the label via email.<br>
<a href="/en/order-processing/fulfilment/preparing-the-shipment#3200">DHL Retoure Online</a> = Customers can create returns, then download and print the DHL return label.<br>
<strong>Deactivated</strong> = Customers can not create returns. If you select this option, then you will need to decide how your company deals with returns. For example, you may require customers to call or send an email if they want to return an item.<br>
If you allow customers to create returns themselves, then they will be able to choose the appropriate <a href="/en/order-processing/orders/managing-sales-orders#return">reason for return</a> in their "My account" area.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Price display for wish list and watchlist</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">There are the following options for displaying prices in the online store: <strong>Item price only</strong>, <strong>Item price with asterisk (</strong>)<strong>, *Price including VAT and shipping</strong><br>
<em>*Tip*</em>: The option <strong>Item price with asterisk (</strong>)* can be used to give additional price information below the asterisk, e.g. to give VAT information.<br>
<em>*Info*</em>: The option <strong>price including VAT and shipping</strong> is required if you want your online store to be certified by Trusted Shops.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Shipping weight in wish list and watchlist</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for displaying the shipping weight in the wish list and watchlist.<br>
<em>*Important*</em>: If you decide to display this information, then go to <a href="/en/_includes/number-formats">System » Settings » Numbers</a> and check the settings for number formats. For example, if <strong>in kilograms: no decimal place</strong> is set here, then weights that are less than 1000 grams will be displayed as 0.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Subscriptions</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for displaying the <strong>Subscription</strong> area.<br>
<em>*Info*</em>: The submenu under <a href="/en/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/cms#web-design-editing-the-web-design-my-account">CMS » Web design » My account</a> becomes visible once this function has been activated.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Payment method: Subscriptions</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select whether customers should be able to <strong>change the payment method</strong> for a subscription.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Download link for SEPA direct debit mandate</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for displaying the download link.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Change email address</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for changing the email address.<br>
In order to change the address, the account’s password has to be entered.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Change password</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for changing the <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users">password</a>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Email confirmation when changing the password</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the automatic email confirmation when the password is changed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Hide logout</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Activate</strong> or <strong>deactivate</strong> the function for displaying the logout.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="order-information">3. Order information</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>System » Client » Select client » My Account » Order information</strong> menu, you specify how much information is displayed in orders.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Configuring order information:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » My Account » Order information</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#table-settings-order-confirmation">Table 2</a> and carry out the settings as desired.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-settings-order-confirmation" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
<caption class="title">Table 2. settings in the <strong>Order information</strong> menu</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 25%;">
<col style="width: 75%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Status history</strong>;<br>
<strong>Shipping date</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select whether or not you would like information regarding the status history and/or the shipping date to be displayed in the order overview.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Weights</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Decide whether or not you want the weights to be shown in the order.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Invoices</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select whether or not customers can download the invoice for the order.<br>
<strong>Disable download for customers</strong> = Customers will not be able to download invoices.<br>
<strong>Enable download of internal invoices for customers</strong> = Customers will only be able to download internal invoices, i.e. invoices for orders placed in the online store.<br>
<strong>Enable download of external invoices for customers</strong> = Customers will not only be able to download internal invoices, but also external invoices, i.e. for example invoices for orders that were placed on markets.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Estimated shipping date</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Select whether or not you would like the estimated shipping date to be displayed in the online store.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
